<biogHist>
<abstract>Scatter cottage was a term used to describe a model of out-of-home care in the 1970s and 1980s. A scatter cottage was a house that was run by an institution but was not on the same property as the main institutional buildings. Usually, up to 10 children lived in a scatter cottage with houseparents.</abstract>

</biogHist>
