<repository>Uniting Church (Synod of Western Australia) Archives</repository>
<unittitle>The 'Homes' Herald, 1970 [Methodist Homes for Children]</unittitle>
<unitdate>December 1970</unitdate>
<abstract><span style="font-style:italic">The 'Homes' Herald</span> was a newsletter of the Methodist Homes for Children. This is a copy of the December 1970 edition. It has a picture of some children playing at Mofflyn and a photo of the front of the Allandale Boys' Cottage at 149 Sussex Street. The news items give a small amount of information about each Home and talk about some planned 'scatter homes'. There is news about the retirement of Matron Roberts and a photo of her with some kindergarten children. The newsletter also appeals for funds, explains how previous support has helped, and lets readers know what more they can do</abstract>
</archref>
